cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing and implementing a concurrent hash table for GPUs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a dynamic non-blocking concurrent linked list and a dynamic hash table with chaining. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of the implementation on an NVIDIA Tesla K40c GPU. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper proposes a warp-cooperative work sharing strategy and a warp-synchronous dynamic memory allocator. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possibility as the paper presents performance results for the implemented hash table and memory allocator.
